 Openbox Window Manager Refresh desktop menu to add new programs, etc. vim ~/.config/openbox/menu.xml
&lt;?xml version=&#34;1.0&#34; encoding=&#34;utf-8&#34;?&gt;
&lt;openbox_menu&gt;
&lt;menu id=&#34;root-menu&#34; label=&#34;OpenBox 3&#34; execute=&#34;/usr/bin/obmenu-generator&#34;&gt;
&lt;/menu&gt;
&lt;/openbox_menu&gt; Center all new windows vim ~/.config/openbox/rc.xml
&lt;placement&gt;
&lt;policy&gt;Smart&lt;/policy&gt;
&lt;!-- &#39;Smart&#39; or &#39;UnderMouse&#39; --&gt;
&lt;center&gt;yes&lt;/center&gt;
&lt;!-- whether to place windows in the center of the free area found or
the top left corner --&gt;
&lt;monitor&gt;Any&lt;/monitor&gt;
&lt;!-- with Smart placement on a multi-monitor system, try to place new windows
on: &#39;Any&#39; - any monitor, &#39;Mouse&#39; - where the mouse is, &#39;Active&#39; - where
the active window is --&gt;
&lt;/placement&gt;

